# Episode 06 – Adding Memory and Conversation Awareness

In this episode, I connected a Simple Memory node to the AI Agent.

Before adding memory, the chatbot could answer questions but could not remember previous messages. After connecting memory, the assistant became capable of maintaining context throughout a conversation.

I tested this by sharing my name, discussing another topic, and then asking the assistant to recall my name. The AI successfully remembered the information.

This helped me understand the difference between business knowledge and conversation memory. Business knowledge comes from prompts and rules, while memory comes from previous messages within the conversation.

Key Learning:
Memory transforms a chatbot from a simple question-answer system into a conversational assistant.
